<h1 class="docs-header">Functions</h1>
<p>This is where we define custom functions for our framework. These functions are global and don't apply specifically to a single element/block.</p>

<!-- #function #strip_units -->

<article id="function-strip_units" class="block block-function" data-type="function">
<h3>strip_units</h3>
<p>Strips the unit from a value. For example, if you pass it 12px, it will strip off the px unit and return the number 12. This function is used in <a href="#px_to_em" class="code-link"><code>@function px_to_em</code></a> and <a href="#em_to_px" class="code-link"><code>@function em_to_px</code></a> to return the proper value.</p>
<div class="example">
  <div class="example-block example-code">
<pre><code class="language-scss">@function strip_units( $val )
  returns: number</code></pre>
  </div><!-- .example-code -->
</div><!-- .example -->

<h4 id="param-column_width">Parameters</h4>

<ul class="param-list">
<li class="param">
<div class="example" id="param-strip_units-val">
  <div class="example-block example-code">
<pre><code class="language-scss">@param: $val
  type: unit (pixel, em, rem)</code></pre>
  </div><!-- .example-code -->
</div><!-- .example -->
<p>The unit you want striped to a number value.</p>
</li>
</ul>

</article>

<!-- #function #px_to_em -->

<article id="function-px_to_em" class="block block-function" data-type="function">
<h3>px_to_em</h3>
<p>Converts a pixel value to EMs. By default it'll use the base font size, but can be passed a custom base font size.</p>
<div class="example">
  <div class="example-block example-code">
<pre><code class="language-scss">@function px_to_em( $px, $base )
  returns: unit (em)</code></pre>
  </div><!-- .example-code -->
</div><!-- .example -->

<h4 id="param-column_width">Parameters</h4>

<ul class="param-list">
<li class="param">
<div class="example" id="param-px_to_em-px">
  <div class="example-block example-code">
<pre><code class="language-scss">@param: $px
  type: unit (pixel, number)</code></pre>
  </div><!-- .example-code -->
</div><!-- .example -->
<p>The pixel unit you want converted to EMs.</p>
</li>
<li class="param">
<div class="example" id="param-px_to_em-base">
  <div class="example-block example-code">
<pre><code class="language-scss">@param: $base
  type: unit (pixel, number)
  default: $base-font-size</code></pre>
  </div><!-- .example-code -->
</div><!-- .example -->
<span class="reference">Reference: <a href="#base-font-size" class="code-link"><code>$base-font-size</code></a></span>
<p>The base font-size that the returned EM value is calculated from.</p>
</li>
</ul>

<h4>Example Usage</h4>

<div class="example">
  <div class="example-block example-code">
    <div class="example-tag">
      <span class="tag tag-lang tag-lang-scss">SCSS</span>
    </div>
<pre><code class="language-scss">h1 {
  font-size: px_to_em(28px);
}

.aside {
  font-size: px_to_em(12px);
  h2 {
    font-size: px_to_em(18px, 12px);
  }
}</code></pre>
  </div><!-- .example-code -->
  <div class="example-block example-code">
    <div class="example-tag">
      <span class="tag tag-lang tag-lang-css">CSS</span>
    </div>
<pre><code class="language-scss">h1 {
  font-size: 2em;
}

.aside {
  font-size: 0.85714em;
}

.aside h2 {
  font-size: 1.5em;
}</code></pre>
  </div><!-- .example-code -->
</div><!-- .example -->

</article>

<!-- #function #em_to_px -->

<article id="function-em_to_px" class="block block-function" data-type="function">
<h3>em_to_px</h3>
<p>Works the same as <a href="#px_to_em" class="code-link"><code>@function px_to_em</code></a> except it converts an EM value to pixels. By default it'll use the base font size, but can be passed a custom base font size.</p>
<div class="example">
  <div class="example-block example-code">
<pre><code class="language-scss">@function em_to_px( $em, $base )
  returns: unit (pixel)</code></pre>
  </div><!-- .example-code -->
</div><!-- .example -->

<h4 id="param-column_width">Parameters</h4>

<ul class="param-list">
<li class="param">
<div class="example" id="param-px_to_em-px">
  <div class="example-block example-code">
<pre><code class="language-scss">@param: $em
  type: unit (em, number)</code></pre>
  </div><!-- .example-code -->
</div><!-- .example -->
<p>The EM unit you want converted to pixels.</p>
</li>
<li class="param">
<div class="example" id="param-px_to_em-base">
  <div class="example-block example-code">
<pre><code class="language-scss">@param: $base
  type: unit (pixel, number)
  default: $base-font-size</code></pre>
  </div><!-- .example-code -->
</div><!-- .example -->
<span class="reference">Reference: <a href="#base-font-size" class="code-link"><code>$base-font-size</code></a></span>
<p>The base font-size that the returned pixel value is calculated from.</p>
</li>
</ul>

</article>